      "to_id": "cec50b17:25",
      "content": "Store the S-Deck theme preference in `.synapse/settings.json` so it persists across dashboard restarts (the random port changes localStorage origin, losing the preference).\n\n**Work inside:** `.synapse/worktrees/developer-25-theme-settings-json`\nCommit your changes to that branch. Do not push.\n\n---\n\n**How it works currently (`public/app.js`):**\n- Theme is read from `localStorage.getItem('sdeck-theme')` — `'bright'` or `'dark'` (default)\n- Toggle writes back to `localStorage.setItem('sdeck-theme', ...)`\n- Problem: random port = different origin each restart = localStorage resets\n\n**What to change:**\n\n**`src/dashboard.ts`** — add two endpoints:\n1. `GET /api/settings` — reads `.synapse/settings.json` and returns `{ theme?: string, ...rest }`\n2. `POST /api/settings` — accepts `{ theme: string }`, merges it into `.synapse/settings.json`\n\nThe settings file path is `join(process.cwd(), '.synapse', 'settings.json')`. Read with `existsSync` + `JSON.parse(readFileSync(...))`, write with `writeFileSync(path, JSON.stringify({...existing, ...update}, null, 2))`.\n\n**`public/app.js`** — change theme init and toggle:\n\nOn load, replace the `localStorage.getItem` call with a fetch to `/api/settings`:\n```js\n// init theme\nfetch('/api/settings').then(r => r.json()).then(s => {\n  if (s.theme === 'bright') document.documentElement.classList.add('bright');\n}).catch(() => {});\n```\n\nOn toggle, replace `localStorage.setItem` with a POST:\n```js\nfetch('/api/settings', {\n  method: 'POST',\n  headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n  body: JSON.stringify({ theme: isBright ? 'dark' : 'bright' }),\n});\n```\n\nKeep the existing `localStorage` calls as a fallback in case the fetch fails (so it still works during development without the server).\n\n**Build:** `npm run build` must pass. Commit. Report DONE to cec50b17:0.",
